			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				~Running around for 40 mins = no mana regeneration.<BR>
<BR>
~Casting root for 40 mins, or any other spell for that matter, will sap all mana.<BR>
<BR>
~PoD would kill a pet very quickly which means resummoning a pet (mana drain); is 41 the highest lvl pet a Necro can summon?  If so there's no way the pet, outclassed by 10+ lvls, smacked the PoD for as much dmg as would have been necessary(nearly 32k HP's).  <BR>
<BR>
~How many HP's are rats going to give you?  That's nonsense.  Why?  There's no way you could have had time to hit more than one rat, targeting and casting, before the PoD was almost on you.  Two tops.<BR>
<BR>
~You admitted LifeTap didn't work on the PoD - more wasted mana.  How many times did you try this spell?  Also you stated the PoD tried to heal himself *9* times but was unsuccessful every time because your pet disrupted the spell.  This again goes to the maximum lvl of the pet.  What is it?  I do know disrupting MoB casters is not an easy thing to do.<BR>
<BR>
~The pic with the dead PoD would be assumed to have been taken very soon after its death to be sure of getting it.  We've all been witness to the almost instantaneous &quot;disappearing corpse&quot;.<BR>
<BR>
~If the Necro had had a sliver of life left and no mana, I'd be closer to believing this by a good margin.<BR>
<BR>
~Just to drive home the pt. about LifeTapping Giant rats while a PoD is DDing you...Look at it like trying to put out a forest fire bucket by bucket from a small stream, you may doing good, but in the long run you will lose.<BR>
<BR>
~So this is where we stand with this topic: 1) The Necro had a lot of mana left over the period of a 40 minute fight, as well as a good deal of HP's; 2) Most of the Necro's spells were ineffective against the PoD, and apparently the Necro was casting much anyway; 3) His pet, max lvl?, kept the PoD from healing himself *and* did 90% of the dmg to the PoD as the necro admitted he was running around LifeTapping rats and casting the occasional root spell to keep the PoD off of his pet.<BR>
<BR>
(~Naelelven: Really stuck on this newbie/lowbie thing, eh?  And as for the 51+ lvl spells, where's the relevence to this discussion?  Thanks for your time, you're dismissed.)
